Title: 1. The Ten Commandments
description: Moses, raised as a prince of Egypt in the Pharaoh's household, learns of his true heritage as a Hebrew and his divine mission as the deliverer of his people from slavery.

Title: 2. Around the World in 80 Days
description: A Victorian Englishman bets that with the new steamships and railways he can circumnavigate the globe in eighty days.

Title: 3. Giant
description: Sprawling epic covering the life of a Texas cattle rancher and his family and associates.

Title: 4. The King and I
description: A widow accepts a job as a live-in governess to the King of Siam's children.

Title: 5. Aparajito
description: Following his father's death, a boy leaves home to study in Calcutta, while his mother must face a life alone.

Title: 6. On the Bowery
description: By focusing on the lives of three down-and-out alcoholic transients, the film creates a wrenching portrait of the tragic hopelessness of life on "The Bowery" in New York City.

Title: 7. The Burmese Harp
description: A conscience-driven Japanese soldier traumatized by the events of WWII adopts the lifestyle of a Buddhist monk.

Title: 8. The Crossing of Paris
description: Two men carry at night four suitcases of contraband meat across German-occupied Paris during WWII. Their opposite personalities and strange encounters provoke different adventures - until they are arrested by the police.

Title: 9. Bob le Flambeur
description: After losing big, an aging gambler decides to assemble a team to rob a casino.

Title: 10. Crime of Passion
description: Kathy leaves the newspaper business to marry homicide detective Bill but is frustrated by his lack of ambition and the banality of life in the suburbs. Her drive to advance Bill's career soon takes her down a dangerous path.

Title: 11. Forbidden Planet
description: A starship crew in the 23rd century goes to investigate the silence of a distant planet's colony, only to find just two survivors, a powerful robot, and the deadly secret of a lost civilization.

Title: 12. The Searchers
description: An American Civil War veteran embarks on a years-long journey to rescue his niece from the Comanches after the rest of his brother's family is massacred in a raid on their Texas farm.

Title: 13. The Wrong Man
description: In 1953, an innocent man named Christopher Emanuel "Manny" Balestrero is arrested after being mistaken for an armed robber.

Title: 14. The Opposite Sex
description: Former nightclub singer Kay Hilliard, married 10 years and mother of a young daughter, is informed that her husband Steven is having an affair with chorus girl Crystal Allen, so she goes to Reno for a divorce.

Title: 15. Invasion of the Body Snatchers
description: A small-town doctor learns that the population of his community is being replaced by emotionless alien duplicates.

Title: 16. The Man Who Knew Too Much
description: An American doctor and his wife, a former singing star, witness a murder while vacationing in Morocco, and are drawn into a twisting plot of international intrigue when their young son is kidnapped.

Title: 17. The Killing
description: Crook Johnny Clay assembles a five-man team to plan and execute a daring racetrack robbery.

Title: 18. The Bad Seed
description: Rhoda Penmark seems like your average, sweet eight-year-old girl. After her rival at school dies in mysterious circumstances at the school picnic, her mother starts to suspect that Rhoda was responsible.

Title: 19. Moby Dick
description: The sole survivor of a lost whaling ship relates the tale of his captain's self-destructive obsession to hunt the white whale, Moby Dick.

Title: 20. Reprisal!
description: Half-breed Frank Madden claims he's White, in order to own land, but violent racial clashes in town force him to abandon his neutrality and chose a side.

Title: 21. The Steel Jungle
description: A power struggle emerges among convicts condemned to prison life.

Title: 22. War and Peace
description: Napoleon's tumultuous relations with Russia, including his disastrous 1812 invasion, serve as the backdrop for the tangled personal lives of two aristocratic families.

Title: 23. The Conqueror
description: Mongol chief Temujin battles against Tartar armies and for the love of the Tartar princess Bortai. Temujin becomes the emperor Genghis Khan.
In a totalitarian future society, Winston Smith, whose daily work is re-writing history, tries to rebel by falling in love.

Title: 25. High Society
description: With socialite Tracy Lord about to remarry, her ex-husband - with the help of a sympathetic reporter - has 48 hours to convince her that she really still loves him.

Title: 26. Baby Doll
description: An immature, naive teenage bride holds her anxious husband at bay while flirting with an amorous Sicilian farmer.

Title: 27. ...And God Created Woman
description: In sunny St. Tropez, a young woman loves one brother but marries the other.

Title: 28. World Without End
description: Astronauts returning from a voyage to Mars are caught in a time warp and are propelled into a post-Apocalyptic Earth populated by mutants.

Title: 29. A Man Escaped
description: A captured French Resistance fighter during World War II engineers a daunting escape from a German prison in France.

Title: 30. The Creature Walks Among Us
description: A scientist captures the Creature and turns him into an air-breather, only for him to escape and start killing.

Title: 31. Bus Stop
description: A naive but stubborn cowboy falls in love with a saloon singer and tries to take her away against her will to get married and live on his ranch in Montana.

Title: 32. The King and Four Queens
description: Opportunistic con man Dan Kehoe ingratiates himself with the cantankerous mother of four outlaws and their beautiful widows in order to find their hidden gold.

Title: 33. Patterns
description: When Fred Staples is recruited onto the board of a high-powered New York corporation, he finds his ethics and ambition at odds.

Title: 34. Lust for Life
description: The life of brilliant but tortured artist Vincent van Gogh.

Title: 35. Friendly Persuasion
description: The pacifist attitude of a Quaker family is tested as a result of the American Civil War.

Title: 36. Written on the Wind
description: Alcoholic playboy Kyle Hadley marries the woman secretly loved by his poor but hard-working best friend, who in turn is pursued by Kyle's sister.

Title: 37. The Man Who Never Was
description: In order to fool the Germans into thinking the Allied invasion of Sicily will take place elsewhere, British Military Intelligence comes up with a cunning ruse.

Title: 38. Anastasia
description: An opportunistic businessman tries to pass off a mysterious impostor as the Grand Duchess Anastasia, and she is so convincing that even the biggest skeptics believe her.

Title: 39. Earth vs. the Flying Saucers
description: Extraterrestrials traveling in high-tech flying saucers contact a scientist as part of a plan to enslave the inhabitants of Earth.

Title: 40. The Harder They Fall
description: An ex-sportswriter is hired by a shady fight promoter to promote his latest find, an unknown but easily exploitable rising star from Argentina.

Title: 41. Nightfall
description: Through a series of bizarre coincidences, an artist finds himself falsely accused of bank robbery and murder and is pursued by the authorities and the real killers.

Title: 42. Carousel
description: Fifteen years after his death, a carousel barker is granted permission to return to Earth for one day to make amends to his widow and their daughter.

Title: 43. Trapeze
description: A crippled circus acrobat is torn emotionally between two ambitious young trapeze artists, one a talented young American and a less-gifted but beautiful Italian.

Title: 44. Somebody Up There Likes Me
description: Boxer Rocky Graziano's biopic, based on his autobiography, from childhood to his World Middleweight Championship title win at age 28 in 1947.

Title: 45. The Great American Pastime
description: Bruce Hallerton becomes coach of the Panthers, a little league baseball team. The fact that an attractive widow has her son in the team causes problems with his wife.

Title: 46. The Girl Can't Help It
description: A gangster hires a down-and-out press agent to make his airheaded girlfriend a singing star.

Title: 47. A Kiss Before Dying
description: A ruthless college student resorts to murder in an attempt to marry an heiress.

Title: 48. Love Me Tender
description: At the end of the Civil War, a Confederate team is ordered to rob a Union payroll train but the war ends leaving these men with their Union loot, until the Feds come looking for it.

Title: 49. Wicked as They Come
description: A poor but beautiful woman sets her sights on rising to the top, and lets nothing stand in her way - including murder.

Title: 50. You Can't Run Away from It
description: After she elopes, Ellen Andrews' rich father hires a private investigator to stop her from reaching her husband, believing he's a gold digger. On her adventurous journey, a reporter falls for her instead of exposing her for the reward.

Title: 51. Sissi - Die junge Kaiserin
description: The second in a trilogy of movies about Elisabeth "Sissi" of Austria, the film chronicles the married life of the young empress as she tries to adjust to formal and strict life in the palace and an overbearing mother-in-law.

Title: 52. The Last Wagon
description: Wagon train survivors of an Apache attack entrust the sheriff's prisoner, scout Comanche Todd, with their lives despite his wanted-for-murder status.

Title: 53. The Fastest Gun Alive
description: In the western frontier town of Cross Creek, storekeeper George Temple is a polite and soft spoken man with a secret past. When 3 bank robbers on the lam stop in town to change horses, George's past comes back to haunt him.

Title: 54. The Power and the Prize
description: An American business executive (Robert Taylor) plans to marry an Austrian refugee (Elisabeth Müller) in London but he encounters disapproval and opposition from his American social and business circles.

Title: 55. Alexander the Great
description: The life and military conquests of Alexander III of Macedon (July 20/21, 356 - June 10/11, 323 B.C.), commonly known as Alexander the Great.

Title: 56. There's Always Tomorrow
description: When a toy manufacturer feels ignored and unappreciated by his wife and children, he begins to rekindle a past love when a former employee comes back into his life.

Title: 57. 7 Men from Now
description: A former sheriff blames himself for his wife's death during a Wells Fargo robbery and vows to track down and kill the seven men responsible.

Title: 58. Tea and Sympathy
description: A new senior at a boy's prep school, finds himself harassed by the machismo culture of his classmates and the unfeelingly behavior by his father, only being treated with decency by his roommate and with affection by the coach's wife.

Title: 59. Passport to Treason
description: While investigating the mysterious death of a friend, a man discovers a peace organization is the front for a crime syndicate. Based on the novel of the same name by Manning O'Brien.

Title: 60. The Violent Years
description: Paula Parkins is the teenage daughter of wealthy parents who can't seem to make time for her, so she looks for thrills as the leader of her all girl-gang who rob and rape young men.

Title: 61. The Sword and the Dragon
description: A mythical knight goes on an epic journey and fights barbarian hordes in an ancient land.

Title: 62. Pursuit of the Graf Spee
description: In the first major naval battle of World War II, the British Navy must find and destroy a powerful German warship.

Title: 63. Nightmare
description: A New Orleans musician has a nightmare about killing a man in a strange house but he suspects that it really happened.

Title: 64. Bigger Than Life
description: A seriously-ill schoolteacher becomes dependent on a "miracle" drug that begins to affect his sanity.

Title: 65. Autumn Leaves
description: A lonely middle-aged woman meets a younger man, but their relationship is threatened after the man's troubled past reveals itself.

Title: 66. The Werewolf
description: Two scientists are involved in a car accident and find an unconscious man in the remains. They take him to their lab and inject him with a serum they have been working with. Sadly, the serum turns the man into a murderous werewolf.

Title: 67. Godzilla: King of the Monsters!
description: An American reporter visiting Tokyo becomes a witness to the city's destruction by a dinosaur-like beast awoken from undersea hibernation by atom bomb testing.

Title: 68. Reach for the Sky
description: Biopic of RAF Group Captain Douglas Bader who, after having lost both legs, flew a British fighter plane during WWII.

Title: 69. The Killer Is Loose
description: An unhinged, deceptively mild-mannered bank robber escapes prison, seeking revenge on the cop who accidentally killed his wife during a gun battle.

Title: 70. The Swan
description: When a crown prince visits, the princess's mother tries to push the prince into marrying her daughter by presenting a "rival" at the ball - her children's handsome tutor.

Title: 71. The Teahouse of the August Moon
description: In post-WWII Japan, an American captain is brought in to help build a school, but the locals want a teahouse instead.

Title: 72. Jubal
description: A new foreman rejects the sexual advances of a frustrated rancher's wife, which leads to conflicts that could get him killed.

Title: 73. Spin a Dark Web
description: A Canadian living in London is trying to succeed as a prizefighter, without much luck. He meets the sister of a local mob leader, and she soon draws him into the gang's activities. After he finds himself being drawn into a murder plot, he finally realizes that his lover is only using him, and determines to escape the gang - but things don't turn out the way he planned.

Title: 74. The She-Creature
description: A mysterious hypnotist reverts his beautiful assistant back into the form of a prehistoric sea monster that she was in a past life.

Title: 75. The Man in the Gray Flannel Suit
description: An ex-soldier faces ethical questions as he tries to earn enough to support his wife and children well.

Title: 76. Backlash
description: Jim Slater seeks a survivor of the Apache ambush his father died in.

Title: 77. Street of Shame
description: The personal tales of various prostitutes who occupy a brothel.

Title: 78. Attack
description: In 1944, an American Infantry company sets up an artillery observation post, but tensions between Captain Cooney and Lieutenant Costa run high.

Title: 79. While the City Sleeps
description: A serial killer has been killing beautiful women in New York City and the new owner of a media company offers a high position in the company to the first of his senior executives who can get the earliest scoop on the case.

Title: 80. The Rainmaker
description: During the Depression, a con-man promises rain to a desperate drought-ridden Kansas town and marriage to a local desperate spinster.

Title: 81. It Conquered the World
description: A well meaning scientist guides an alien monster to Earth from Venus, so that he can rid mankind of feelings and emotions - but only death and sorrow results.

Title: 82. The Last Hunt
description: In 1883 South Dakota, two buffalo hunters start a personal feud over a captured squaw and a stand-off with a Dakota raiding party over some stolen horses.

Title: 83. Early Spring
description: A young man and his wife struggle within the confines of their passionless relationship while he has an extramarital romance.

Title: 84. Foreign Intrigue
description: When a reclusive, enigmatic millionaire dies suddenly on the Riviera, his press agent begins to investigate his employer's shady past.

Title: 85. The Lone Ranger
description: Wealthy rancher Reese Kilgore aims to grab silver-rich Indian land by skilfully pitting Indians against settlers but the suspicious territorial governor sends The Lone Ranger to investigate.

Title: 86. The Scarlet Hour
description: An unhappy wife uses her powers of manipulation to draw an infatuated man into an ill-fated jewelry heist.

Title: 87. The Green Man
description: An assassin is annoyed by a vacuum cleaner salesman determined to stop him.

Title: 88. The Mole People
description: A party of archaeologists discovers the remnants of a mutant five-millennia-old Sumerian civilization living beneath a glacier atop a mountain in Mesopotamia.

Title: 89. Curucu, Beast of the Amazon
description: A doctor and an adventurer journey to the Amazon, where they encounter a man in a bizarre bird costume terrorizing the local indigenous population.

Title: 90. Hollywood or Bust
description: A singer who can't pay his bookie joins a nerdy, star-struck movie fan and his Great Dane in a cross-country convertible ride to Hollywood.

Title: 91. The Burning Hills
description: After Trace Jordan's brother is murdered by members of the land-grabbing Sutton family, he vows to report this injustice to the nearest Army fort.

Title: 92. A Town Like Alice
description: A newly wealthy English woman returns to Malaya to build a well for the villagers who helped her during war. Thinking back, she recalls the Australian man who made a great sacrifice to aid her and her fellow prisoners of war.

Title: 93. 23 Paces to Baker Street
description: A blind American writer living in London stumbles upon a criminal conspiracy involving kidnapping and extortion.

Title: 94. Bhowani Junction
description: Anglo-Indian Victoria Jones seeks her true identity amid the chaos of the British withdrawal from India.

Title: 95. The Mountain
description: Selfish Chris Teller pressures his older brother, a retired climber, to accompany him on a treacherous Alpine climb to loot the bodies of plane crash victims.

Title: 96. Gunslinger
description: After her husband is gunned down, Rose Hood takes his place temporarily as Marshal of a small Western town.

Title: 97. The Brave One
description: A young boy named Leonardo adopts a bull after saving it during a storm, but their friendship is soon threatened by the legal owners of the animal who claim ownership of it and ship it off to the bullring to face a legendary bullfighter.

Title: 98. Pillars of the Sky
description: In 1868 Oregon, after the Army violates the treaty by building a road across the reservation, several tribal chiefs decide to unite their forces against the trespassing whites.

Title: 99. The Lieutenant Wore Skirts
description: Former military man fails medical exam for re-enlistment. His wife joins Air Force, excelling in her role. Unhappy as a househusband, he travels to Hawaii to devise a plan to get her discharged.

Title: 100. The Revolt of Mamie Stover
description: Set in the early '40s, a San Francisco prostitute is run out of town just as the second World War has begun to intensify. Mamie settles down in Hawaii, hoping to start a new life. Though her prospects look good when she falls in love with a science-fiction writer who treats her with the respect she deserves, the dawning war and the fallacies of her previous lifestyle complicate their budding romance. Mamie cannot fully remove herself from her former profession, and provides some of her old services to the sailors stationed in town. Searching for another means of financial security, Mamie invests in several pieces of real estate and becomes quite wealthy, though her bad reputation has not been forgotten by the locals.

Title: 101. Beyond a Reasonable Doubt
description: A novelist aided by his future father-in-law conspires to frame himself for the murder of a burlesque dancer as part of an effort to ban capital punishment.

Title: 102. Away All Boats
description: The story of a U.S. Naval ship and its crew in the Pacific, from 1943 to 1945.

Title: 103. The Proud and Profane
description: In the Pacific during WWII, a Roman Catholic widow falls for a tough lieutenant colonel.

Title: 104. The Hunchback of Notre Dame
description: The timeless tale of the seductive gypsy Esmeralda and the tortured hunchback Quasimodo.

Title: 105. Helen of Troy
description: The Iliad's story of the Trojan war, told from the Trojan viewpoint.

Title: 106. Port Afrique
description: Rip Reardon, ex-Army flier, returns to his home in French Morocco and finds his wife dead, and he suspects she has been murdered. Police Colonel Moussac insists she committed suicide. Rip begins to suspect not only his friends but also a mysterious brunette, Ynez, a Casbah night-club singer with whom he begins to fall in love. Repeated efforts to kill Rip are made but he ultimately finds the evidence which sends him gunning against the killer...but is he mistaken?

Title: 107. Rodan
description: A mining engineer investigates the deaths of his colleagues, discovering prehistoric nymphs and a creature capable of flying - and wreaking havoc - at supersonic speeds.

Title: 108. Please Murder Me!
description: A lawyer suffers a guilt complex after getting a murder acquittal for his client, and then finding out she did commit the crime.

Title: 109. The Beast of Hollow Mountain
description: An American cowboy living in Mexico discovers his cattle are being eaten by a giant prehistoric dinosaur.

Title: 110. X the Unknown
description: A radioactive, mud-like creature terrorizes a Scottish village.

Title: 111. Meet Me in Las Vegas
description: In 1950s Las Vegas, a gambling rancher and a ballerina discover that some people have luck at cards while others have luck at love.

Title: 112. The Great Locomotive Chase
description: During the Civil War Union spy Andrews and his men volunteer to steal a Confederate train and drive it to Union territory while destroying the Confederate railway system along the way.

Title: 113. Never Say Goodbye
description: In 1945 Vienna, an American doctor marries an Austrian girl, who later disappears in the Soviet Control Zone during a visit there, forcing everyone to presume her dead.

Title: 114. Liane, Jungle Goddess
description: When Liane, a lost girl worshiped by an African tribe, is returned to her native Hamburg, she becomes the center of a love quadrangle and a deadly tug-of-war over her grandfather's inheritance.

Title: 115. Pardners
description: A rich momma's boy returns west with the son of his murdered father's partner to foil a gang trying to gain control of his family ranch.

Title: 116. The Catered Affair
description: When Jane Hurley tells her parents Tom (a struggling cab driver) and Agnes (a domestic engineer) that she is marrying Ralph Halloran, Agnes starts planning a big wedding, even though Jane and Ralph don't want it and Tom cannot afford it.

Title: 117. Lisbon
description: High stakes battle of wits and morals between gentlemen crooks, set in beautiful Portugal. A smuggler is hired to kidnap the rich husband of an American woman who's just arrived in Lisbon.

Title: 118. The Bitter Stems
description: A washed up reporter teams up with an immigrant from Hungary to start a fake journalism by correspondence school.

Title: 119. Davy Crockett and the River Pirates
description: Davy and his friends leave for New Orleans to sell some fur pelts.

Title: 120. Elena and Her Men
description: Polish countess Elena falls in love with a French radical party's candidate - a general - in pre-World War I Paris, but another officer pines for her. Starring Ingrid Bergman, with Mel Ferrer and Jean Marais as the rivals for her affection.

Title: 121. Three Bad Sisters
description: A millionaire dies in an airplane crash, leaving all of his money to be divided among his three daughters. One of the daughters doesn't want to share any of it, so she plans to get rid of her two sisters.

Title: 122. Girls in Prison
description: Anne Carson, meeting the seamy side of prison life, finds that everyone thinks she knows where unrecovered bank loot is.

Title: 123. Run for the Sun
description: In Central America, an action-adventure novelist and a journalist for a magazine find themselves at the mercy of Nazi war criminals.

Title: 124. Gervaise
description: A poor laundrywoman tries to cope with a depressing burden of society.

Title: 125. Battle Stations
description: The crew of a U.S. Navy ship in World War II goes into battle against the Japanese fleet.

Title: 126. Gun the Man Down
description: Two bank robbers abandon their wounded partner to the posse and run with the loot but their partner, after serving time in prison, seeks revenge.

Title: 127. The Eddy Duchin Story
description: The life story of the famous pianist and band leader of the 1930s and 1940s.

Title: 128. The Benny Goodman Story
description: The young Benny Goodman is taught clarinet by a Chicago music professor. He is advised by bandleader Kid Ory to play whichever kind of music he likes best, but to make a living, Benny begins by joining the Ben Pollack traveling band.

Title: 129. These Wilder Years
description: A middle-aged man tries to reconnect with his illegitimate son, who was given to an orphanage many years ago.

Title: 130. Nero's Mistress
description: Nero is on holiday at the seaside. Poppea, Seneca and many other guests are with him. Nero is preparing a great show where he will be the star. When Agrippina, his mother, arrives with her German praetorians and decides Nero has to conquer Britain, she is asking for trouble. Many attempts of murder and poisoning will happen on the eve of his great show.

Title: 131. Hot Rod Girl
description: After his kid brother is killed in a street race, a champion drag-racer quits racing. However, a new kid comes to town determined to force him back into racing so he can take his title--and he's already taken his girlfriend.

Title: 132. Naughty Girl
description: Nightclub entertainer Jean Clery discovers too late that the 'baby' he agreed to take care of is a wild, shapely sex kitten.

Title: 133. Anything Goes
description: Two producers find different actresses in Paris for the same Broadway role. Each promises her the part without telling the other. Drama unfolds on their ocean voyage back when both women learn the truth.

Title: 134. Indestructible Man
description: A brutal death row inmate double-crossed by his crooked lawyer gets his chance for revenge when, following his execution, a bizarre experiment brings him back to life and deadlier than ever.

Title: 135. Samurai III: Duel at Ganryu Island
description: Musashi Miyamoto is challenged to a duel by a confident swordsman Sasaki Kojiro. He agrees to fight him in a year's time.

Title: 136. Crime in the Streets
description: Social worker tries to befriend local slum gang.

Title: 137. The Rack
description: A decorated Korean War hero inexplicably collaborates with the enemy while interred in a POW camp and is court-martialed.

Title: 138. The Black Sleep
description: Sir Joel Cadman, a mad scientist, kidnaps his victims and cuts open their brains in an effort to discover a means to cure his wife's brain tumor.

Title: 139. Death of a Scoundrel
description: The New York police investigates the murder of a Czech immigrant whose rags-to-riches story is told by his secretary to homicide detectives.

Title: 140. Outside the Law
description: An ex-con is given the chance to redeem himself, and revenge the murder of an old army buddy, by going undercover in Germany and helping the authorities break up a ring of international counterfeiters who will stop at nothing, including murder, to protect their operation.

Title: 141. Rock Rock Rock!
description: Dori is trying to get together enough money to buy a strapless gown; Daddy has cut off Dori's allowance, but gee, she's gotta go to the prom.

Title: 142. The Mystery of Picasso
description: A filmed record of Pablo Picasso painting numerous canvases for the camera, allowing us to see his creative process at work.

Title: 143. Plucking the Daisy
description: A Paris schoolgirl unwittingly ignites hellfire in the minds of men from Seine to Sorbonne.

Title: 144. The Maverick Queen
description: A Pinkerton detective goes undercover to infiltrate a gang of thieves whose boss is a feisty lady saloonkeeper. Complications ensue.

Title: 145. The Gamma People
description: An American reporter smells a story when he is stranded in an Iron Curtain country where the local dictator is using gamma rays to transform children into mutated henchmen.

Title: 146. Come Next Spring
description: In 1920s Arkansas, after a 12 year absence, reformed alcoholic Matt Ballot returns to his abandoned family but has to win them back and regain his hometown's respect too.

Title: 147. The Forty-First
description: An unexpected romance occurs for a female Red Army sniper and a White Army officer.

Title: 148. Hilda Crane
description: Twice divorced Hilda Crane, feeling she's run out of chances, returns to her mother's house in her small hometown and tries to decide what to do next while still hoping to hold onto her independence. That proves to be a challenge.

Title: 149. Death in the Garden
description: Adventurer Shark comes to a small village near a diamond-miners' camp, and local police arrest him, accusing him of having committed a bank robbery in a neighboring town. The police also confiscate the diamond mine for the state, which incites the miners to revolt, but they're defeated. Shark, Father Lizzardi, Castin, his daughter, and Djin, a whore Castin loves, flee into the jungle and fight for their lives.

Title: 150. 5 Steps to Danger
description: During the 1950s, a man's car trip from L.A. to Texas turns into a Cold-War espionage drama after his car breaks down and he accepts a lift from a stranger.

Title: 151. Raw Edge
description: In 1842 in lawless Oregon, a gunfighter seeks vengeance after his innocent brother is lynched and his beautiful Indian wife is claimed by the local tyrant.

Title: 152. Ransom!
description: After the child of wealthy parents gets abducted, the police and a member of the press intervene to assist the parents in their search but end up complicating their impending decisions.

Title: 153. Glory
description: Clarabel lives on a Kentucky horse farm and has a special love for the filly Glory. With the help of Chad, Clarabel can prevent Glory's sale and keep her to train her and eventually enter her for the Kentucky Derby.

Title: 154. Daniel Boone, Trail Blazer
description: Daniel Boone leads settlers into Kentucky, but must battle Shawnee Indians who have been persuaded by a French renegade that Boone and the settlers are there to kill them and steal their land.

Title: 155. Crazed Fruit
description: Spending their summer on an exotic beach, two brothers fall for the same beautiful girl, whose charm and looks may hide more than they they bargained for.

Title: 156. Back from Eternity
description: After a commercial plane crash lands in a South American jungle, the passengers and pilots must patch up the engines and escape the cannibal-infested area.

Title: 157. Main Street
description: A couple of friends decide to have a good time and play a trick on an unmarried woman. Therefore one of them has to pretend to fall in love with her.

Title: 158. A Cry in the Night
description: A deranged man kidnaps the nubile daughter of a police captain.

Title: 159. Esa voz es una mina
description: A young miner faces the hardships of life singing to cheer up all around him. A promoter casually overhears him sing, and offers him a contract to tour the country.

Title: 160. The Solid Gold Cadillac
description: A minority stockholder takes on the crooked board of directors at a billion dollar corporation.

Title: 161. The Silent World
description: A documentary about the undersea explorers and how they penetrate into the underwater world.

Title: 162. Serenade
description: Damon Vincenti, a young vineyard worker, has a beautiful tenor voice and dreams of becoming a great opera singer. He debuts at Lardelli's Italian restaurant in San Francisco, where he is spotted by Kendall Hale, a society girl who enjoys launching young artists while making them her lovers before dumping them after use. Damon is no exception to the rule: he becomes famous but Kendall leaves him abruptly. He feels so affected that he must give up singing. In Mexico, where he has got back in touch with his inner self, Damon meets Juana Montès.They are happy and get married. But Kendall is still around...

Title: 163. The Trapp Family
description: A novice nun, Maria, is sent to care for the unruly children of a wealthy baron. The baron and Maria fall in love, Maria leaves the convent, and they marry. Under Maria's guidance the family becomes a nationally acclaimed singing group, but when the baron is commissioned to join the German army the family flees to the United States where they endeavor to become established as singers once again. Based upon the true story of the Von Trapp family.

Title: 164. The Third Key
description: The sleuths of Scotland Yard try to solve a series of burglaries.

Title: 165. Between Heaven and Hell
description: The spoiled rich son of a wealthy Southerner is changed by his experiences in the Pacific during World War II.

Title: 166. The Unguarded Moment
description: A beautiful teacher is protective of a high school boy who sexually harassed her, and later he becomes a murder suspect.

Title: 167. Chori Chori
description: A spoiled rich girl on the run travels with a reporter looking for a news scoop.

Title: 168. Safari
description: During the Mau Mau Uprising in British Kenya in the 1950s, settler-hunter Ken Duffield is a hired to guide a lion-hunting-party, but he also hopes to find the Mau Mau rebel who killed his family.

Title: 169. Blackjack Ketchum, Desperado
description: While doing a good deed, the title hero has to shoot a man in self defense, and go into hiding. His peace is interrupted when a cattle baron rides into his territory, and decides to settle there. When no locals want to sell, Jared Tetlow turns to murdering the locals with his hired gun Dee Havalik, and starting a range war. Blackjack finds he has to kill the Tetlow gang off one by one, to restore peace in this movie sharing nothing in common with its real-name historical outlaw.

Title: 170. Storm Center
description: During the 1950s, a small-town librarian is shunned by the locals after she refuses the City Council's request to remove a book on Communism from the library's shelves.

Title: 171. Hot Cars
description: A salt-of-earth family man needs money for his sick son, and decides to keep a job at a used car lot despite realizing it is selling stolen cars.

Title: 172. Qivitoq
description: In this visual masterpiece and first Oscar nominated Danish film, young teacher Eva arriving in Greenland, surprising her fiancée in the arms of a woman. Seeking refuge, she meets a man also carrying a broken heart in the scenic landscape.

Title: 173. Slightly Scarlet
description: An urban wheeler-dealer gets involved in organized crime, corrupt city politics and graft while falling in love with the fiancée of the newly elected mayor.

Title: 174. Walk the Proud Land
description: An agent sent from Washington in 1874 takes charge of an Apache reservation and has the oppressive US Army back off, which creates conflicts and causes the Indians to have great respect for him.

Title: 175. Time Table
description: In Arizona, a train's baggage car is robbed of a large payroll, prompting an investigation led by a railroad official-insurance investigator team.

Title: 176. Swamp Women
description: An undercover policewoman helps three female convicts escape from prison so that they can lead her to a stash of stolen diamonds hidden in a swamp.

Title: 177. The Gentle Touch
description: The public and private lives of 5 girls, who start out as student nurses in the National Health service during the 1950's.

Title: 178. Hot Blood
description: Stephen Torino (Wilde), who is tricked by his brother Marco (Adler) into an arranged marriage with tempestuous Annie Caldash (Russell). Annie is willing to give the union a go, but Torino wants none of it.

Title: 179. Crime Against Joe
description: A disreputable Korean War veteran is suspected of murder.

Title: 180. The Railroad Man
description: The railroad engineer Andrea Marcocci has been working with his partner and friend Gigi Liverani for thirty years and feels happy and proud of his work, drinking wine after hours with his friends in a bar owned by the former railroad man Ugo. Andrea is married to Sara, and his young son Sandro is very close to him; however, Andrea has issues with his unemployed son Marcello and with his pregnant daughter Giulia, whose boyfriend Renato Borghi was forced to marry her. After a suicide crosses the tracks of his train in a curve, Andrea feels deeply affected by the accident and almost collides with another train. The railroad company investigates the accident and steps Andrea down from his position. The domestic life of Andrea is also affected by his aggressive behavior and Marcello and Giulia leave home. Later Andrea also leaves home and starts to drink until the day Sandro visits him in a bar.

Title: 181. Julie
description: A terrified wife tries to escape from her insanely jealous husband who is bent on killing her.

Title: 182. Miracle in the Rain
description: Wartime romance about a lonely man and woman who meet one rainy afternoon in New York.

Title: 183. Finger of Guilt
description: A married movie studio executive's life starts to unravel when he is stalked by a seductively beautiful woman he claims he does not know.

Title: 184. Star in the Dust
description: A sheriff planning on legally hanging a killer, has to contend with farmers who want to lynch him, and cattlemen who want to help him escape.

Title: 185. The Roof
description: A married couple learns that it is possible to build an illegal house in the outskirts of Rome, as long as it is erected in one single night and has a roof.

Title: 186. The Captain from Köpenick
description: A young shoemaker is arrested for stealing a small amount of money, and is released after being jailed for 15 years. He wants to have a pass to get a job and start anew, but without a job he doesn't get a pass; and without a pass, he doesn't get a job. He gets into the net of Prussian bureaucracy, and can't see a solution. Until he enters a small Second-Hand Shop, and sees a Prussian Uniform that fits him like a second skin...

Title: 187. The Boss
description: Political corruption is vividly depicted as a ruthless WWI veteran takes almost complete control of a state with the help of a crooked lawyer. The film is enhanced by John Payne's persuasive performance as "The Boss."

Title: 188. Don't Knock the Rock
description: A disc jockey tries to prove to teenagers' parents that rock 'n' roll is harmless and won't turn their kids into juvenile delinquents.

Title: 189. The Blonde Witch
description: Brulard, a French civil engineer on assignment in Sweden for a lumber company meets Ina, a local nature-girl type, falls in love, has an affair, tries to convert her to "civilization", but ends up getting her killed by superstitious villagers instead.

Title: 190. C.I.D.
description: A newspaper editor gets murdered when he was about to expose the underworld links of a rich person. So, a C.I.D inspector gets assigned to investigate the murder case.

Title: 191. The Ogre of Athens
description: A peaceful, frightened little man is mistakenly identified as "the dragon", a notorious criminal at large. He briefly and reluctantly rules the underworld until they realize their mistake.

Title: 192. Rock, Pretty Baby!
description: Jimmy Daley and Angelo Barrato are teenage members of a band who learn of a contest that they believe will bring them fame. Jimmy must fight the opposition of his father and his feelings for the lovely Joan.

Title: 193. Magic Fire
description: The life and career of German composer Richard Wagner.

Title: 194. Michael Strogoff
description: In 19th century Russia, a Tartar rebellion led by Feofar Khan separates Russia from Siberia where the Tsar's brother and his troops are making a last stand. The Tsar entrusts Captain Michel Strogoff to deliver a vital message to them.

Title: 195. O Olmasin, Bu Olsun
description: Popularly known by the name of the main character, "Mashadi Ibad" was based on a musical comedy by composer Uzeyir Hajibeyov and written in the early 1900s. The story is based on the age old-theme of a beautiful young woman (Gulnaz) who falls in love with a young man (Sarvar) but is obliged to marry someone else. Gulnaz' father, Rustam bey, is bankrupt. He decides that the only way to pay off his creditors is to get money by marrying off Gulnaz to the rich, old, widowed bazaar merchant, Mashadi Ibad. But Sarvar contrives a way to foil the plan by disguising himself as the bride hidden under the thick Muslim veil. When Mashadi Ibad lifts the veil to see his bride's face, he discovers Sarvar who holds him at gun point and makes him write a statement that he really wants to marry the maid, not Gulnaz. This is where the work gets its title, "If Not This One, Then That One." The strategy works and Sarvar succeeds in marrying Gulnaz.

Title: 196. Yield to the Night
description: Locked in her cell, a murderer reflects on the events that have led her to death row.

Title: 197. Hell in Korea
description: During the Korean War retreat in 1951, a small British recon group is surrounded by Chinese troops and holds out in a lonely temple atop a hill.

Title: 198. Toward the Unknown
description: At the dawn of supersonic flight in the 1950s, a group of Edwards Air Force Base experimental aircraft test pilots push themselves to the limit.

Title: 199. Deadlier Than the Male
description: André Chatelin is a restaurant owner in Les Halles in Paris. One morning, a girl named Catherine asks to see him. She happens to be the daughter of his estranged wife, Gabrielle, that André left more than twenty years before. As Gabrielle has just died, André accepts to accommodate Catherine first, then gives her a job in his restaurant before finally marrying her. But the angel-faced young lady might well be a devil in disguise.

Title: 200. Three Men in a Boat
description: Three London gentlemen take a vacation rowing down the Thames, encountering various mishaps and misadventures along the way.

Title: 201. Three Violent People
description: When Confederate officer Colt Saunders returns to his Texas ranch after the war he finds his lands wanted by carpetbaggers and by corrupt provisional government commissioners Harrison and Cable.

Title: 202. Shabab emraa
description: A young man from the country arrives in Cairo to finish his education. His landlady, a widow and successful businesswoman in the quarter of the Citadel, seduces him. Although she teaches him much about life she also makes him forget his obligations to his family, his studies, even his religion. When he tries to put her aside she attempts to force him to give up everything in which he believes.

Title: 203. The Proud Ones
description: Marshal Cass Silver has to deal with his old nemesis, a corrupt gambler, and his hired guns come to town as well as recurring bouts of blindness.

Title: 204. Fire Maidens of Outer Space
description: A team of astronauts lands on a moon of Jupiter to find it populated with beautiful young women looking for mates. An old man explains to the explorers the group's story, as well as the moon's dangers.

Title: 205. Our Miss Brooks
description: Follows the story of an English teacher that flusters the principal and flirts with a colleague.

Title: 206. The Women of Pitcairn Island
description: Eighteen years have passed since the arrival of the Bounty mutineers on Pitcairn Island. The last of these mutineers has just died and the island is now populated solely by their widows and children including Thursday October Christian, son of Fletcher Christian. Onto this island now comes a band of shipwrecked sailors, bringing with them a lust for women and a greed for black pearls.

Title: 207. Dakota Incident
description: Indians attack a stagecoach, and a disparate group of passengers must band together to fight them off.

Title: 208. Her Bridal Night
description: A country girl is discovered by a Paris magazine and becomes a top model.

Title: 209. Hold Back the Night
description: A Marine officer tells his squad the story behind a bottle of liquor that he always keeps with him but never drinks from.

Title: 210. Forever, Darling
description: TV's great comedy duo, Lucille Ball and Desi Arnaz, star in this madcap comedy about a research chemist whose dedicated pursuit of a new pesticide wreaks havoc on his marriage.

Title: 211. Good-bye, My Lady
description: An old man and a young boy who live in the southeastern Mississippi swamps are brought together by the love of a dog.

Title: 212. Tension at Table Rock
description: An infamous gunslinger ends up in Table Rock where the sheriff needs help standing up to cowboys and town elders.

Title: 213. Santiago
description: A gun runner, dishonorably discharged from the military, is swept deeper into a revolution in Cuba after he crosses paths with an enemy from the past and a beautiful revolutionary and her brother.

Title: 214. This is Called Dawn
description: On a Mediterranean island, an honorable doctor hides a hunted criminal. The doctor is soon hunted by a police commissioner.

Title: 215. What a Woman!
description: A photographer named Corrado snaps a picture of Antonietta. When it shows up on the front page of a magazine, she wants to take him to court over it.

Title: 216. The Young Guns
description: The son of a feared Wyoming gunslinger struggles with the decision of whether to follow in his dead father footsteps--as everyone assumes he will--or fight against the pressure of the people he knows, and to break with the past and lead a peaceful life.

Title: 217. Bandido!
description: An arms dealer and a mercenary cross swords during the 1916 Mexican revolution.

Title: 218. Rock Around the Clock
description: A frustrated big-band promoter bumps into rock-and-rollers Bill Haley and the Comets.

Title: 219. Who Done It?
description: This movie debut for saucy British TV comic Benny Hill has Benny leaving his job as a sweeper after winning some money. He becomes a private detective and investigates a plot to assassinate British scientists.

Title: 220. Red Sundown
description: A gunfighter takes a deputy sheriff job in a town caught in a feud between a powerful rancher and small farmers.

Title: 221. Seven Wonders of the World
description: Lowell Thomas searches the world for natural and man made wonders and invites the audience to try to update the ancient Greek list of "Seven Wonders of the World."

Title: 222. The Houston Story
description: In Houston, a man working as an oil driller comes up with a scheme for stealing millions of dollars worth of oil from the fields. He insinuates himself with a local mobster in order to get financing for his scheme.

Title: 223. Beyond Mombasa
description: An American travels to East Africa, where he tries to find out how his brother died.

Title: 224. Adam and Eve
description: Adam and Eve are placed by God in Paradise, but because of the world-infamous sin they committed, God decides to teach them a lesson.

Title: 225. 7th Cavalry
description: An officer accused of cowardice volunteers to bring back General Custers's body after Little Big Horn.

Title: 226. Naked Gun
description: Don Pablo Salazar steals a fortune in jewels from an Indian tribe and an Aztec medicine man puts a curse on the jewels until they are returned. Years later an American insurance man, Breen Mathews (Willard Parker) promises to deliver the Salazar fortune to the rightful heir after Luis Salazar, son of Don Pablo, is killed. Breen heads for Topaz, where he hopes to find the surviving heir, Teresa. He finds instead, Louisa, daughter of Teresa, and is forced to fight a crooked group of townspeople, who are after the Salazar fortune, cursed or otherwise. Included in the group are Judge Cole (Billy House), known as "the Hanging Judge" and Barnum (Barton MacLane), local saloon owner. After defeating all the crooks, Breen is told by Louisa that she, the last of the Salazars, is going to return the treasure to its rightful owners, and lift the curse.

Title: 227. The Ambassador's Daughter
description: The daughter of the American ambassador to France comes to the aid of American soldiers after a grumpy U. S. senator thinks about closing off Paris to the servicemen.

Title: 228. Tribute to a Bad Man
description: With no law within 200 miles horse rancher Jeremy Rodak runs his spread with an iron hand and deals with rustlers even more ruthlessly.

Title: 229. Stay Alert
description: An innocent guy who has arrived from a village to Kolkata gets himself involved into trouble in search of water after he gets thirsty in the middle of the night.

Title: 230. Accused of Murder
description: Police detective Roy Hargis falls for night club singer Ilona Vance, but his partner Sgt. Lackey is convinced she fatally shot mob lawyer Frank Hobart. Hargis has his doubts, until he learns that Ilona once owned the murder weapon.

Title: 231. The First Traveling Saleslady
description: In the late 1800s, 2 east coast sales ladies decide to stop selling corsets and head West to sell barbed wire to Texas cowboys but they face opposition from big ranchers who fear that steel wire would hurt cattle.

Title: 233. Stars in Your Eyes
description: A group of talented young performers buy a dilapidated theatre to showcase their acts - but unscrupulous property developers plan dirty tricks to disrupt the first night's performance.

Title: 234. The Flesh Merchant
description: A girl visiting her sister in Hollywood hopes for a modeling career, but is tricked by pimps into working at a brothel.

Title: 235. Great Day in the Morning
description: A Confederate drifter wins a hotel saloon at poker in Denver but two rival female admirers, local Union sympathizers, Southern gold miners and an orphaned boy complicate his life.

Title: 236. The Iron Petticoat
description: Russian Captain defects to England, not for politics but due to gender discrimination. English Captain ordered to sell capitalism. Defector argues communism better. They fall in love despite KGB attempts to retrieve her.

Title: 237. D-Day the Sixth of June
description: En route to Normandy, an American and a British officer reminisce in flashback about their romances with the same woman.

Title: 238. Warning from Space
description: UFOs are seen around Tokyo. Because they look like giant starfish the aliens cannot approach us without creating panic. Hence one of them sacrifices itself and takes the form of a popular female singer. It/she warns mankind that a meteor will crash on Earth. While the approaching meteor causes hotter and hotter weather, mankind runs and builds a last-chance anti-meteor weapon.

Title: 239. Shadow of the Guillotine
description: While Louis XV is dying, the Dauphine of France, Marie-Antoinette, seduces a Swedish officer, Axel de Fersen, which pains her husband, the new King Louis XVI, who will know how to be generous when he learns of this deception.

Title: 240. The Montecarlo Story
description: A deeply-in-debt gambler sets his cap for a beautiful woman, not knowing that she is also penniless.

Title: 241. The Wild Party
description: A night of terror in a sleazy nightspot, when an over-the-hill football star holds a thrill-seeking couple captive.

Title: 242. Zarak
description: An Afghan outlaw finally saves a British officer at the cost of his own life.

Title: 243. The Weapon
description: A boy accidentally shoots a friend with a gun he found in the rubble of a destroyed building. The gun turns out to be a clue in a ten-year-old murder case.

Title: 244. Bundle of Joy
description: After finding a baby outside an orphanage, a salesgirl receives sympathy from those around her, including her boss' son, as they all assume the baby is hers.

Title: 245. Westward Ho, the Wagons!
description: The adventures of a group of pioneers as their wagon train crosses the West.

Title: 246. The Sharkfighters
description: During World War II, U.S. Navy scientists working in Cuba attempt to find an effective shark repellent to be used by servicemen stranded in shark-infested waters.

Title: 247. Full of Life
description: Writer Nick Rocco and wife Emily face financial strain after buying a house. Needing repairs, they must ask Nick's traditional Italian father for help, leading to tensions over lifestyle choices and values as they expect their first child.

Title: 248. Invitation to the Dance
description: Three different stories are told through a notably unusual way - no words, just dance.

Title: 249. Miami Exposé
description: Miami cop Bart Scott tracks down, in Cuba, a fugitive witness who can shed light in a double homicide and about the activities of a Miami mob lawyer who uses murder and blackmail in order to force the legalization of gambling in Florida.

Title: 250. The Silken Affair
description: Spoiler: Roger Tweakham, a married accountant leading a humdrum life, gets involved with a motivating model, tweaks the books of a stocking factory whose owner he likes so it will show a paper profit and stave off bankruptcy. He then juggles the books of a rival firm whose owner he detests, to show it, on paper, teetering on the edge of ruin. His book-cooking is soon discovered, but by buying the stocks of the first one and then the other, he finds himself in control of both. After a tangle with the law and a farce of a trial, he takes over both operations, merges the two, with the former owners as his partners, kisses the model goodbye and returns to his unsuspecting wife.

Title: 251. Quincannon, Frontier Scout
description: A young woman hires a frontier scout to help her discover if her brother died in an Indian attack on a remote fort.

Title: 252. The Bold and the Brave
description: An assortment of American types come together in the Italian campaign of 1944.

Title: 253. Behind the High Wall
description: A group of convicts break out of prison, killing a guard, kidnapping the warden and forcing a reluctant inmate to accompany them. However, when a car accident kills everyone except the warden and the inmate hostage, the warden steals $100,000 of the gang's money, then when police arrive he accuses the inmate of the guard's murder in order to cover up his own crime.

Title: 254. A Girl in Black
description: Against the backdrop of a cloudless summer, love's unforeseen complications will entwine an Athenian writer, a morosely beautiful daughter, and a scorned local suitor. And then, calamity strikes. Can love redeem the sad girl in black?

Title: 255. The Search for Bridey Murphy
description: After being shown what hypnotism can do, a doctor starts to study it in depth. He experiments on a friend's wife, and she regresses into an early life - that of Bridey Murphy. Several hypnotic sessions explore the life and death of this 19th-century Irishwoman who lived in Cork and Belfast from 1778 until 1864, and the doctor attempts to verify that Bridey Murphy really existed.

Title: 256. Showdown at Abilene
description: After the Civil War, Confederate Jim Trask returns to his native Abilene to find his sweetheart engaged to his old friend Dave Mosely who's leading the cattlemen in a feud against the farmers.

Title: 257. Man from Del Rio
description: A fast Mexican-American gunman kills a few notorious gunfighters and is hired to replace Mesa's dead sheriff but a crooked saloon-keeper wants him on his payroll or out-of-the-way.

Title: 258. The Big Money
description: Petty thief Willie Frith steals a suitcase full of bank notes, only to find out that they have all been given the same serial number. But this is only the start of his troubles: now he must find a way of changing the notes so he can impress the barmaid of his local pub.

Title: 259. El Vaquero and the Girl
description: Her name is María, but everyone knows her by the nickname of The Cat. Daughter of the overseer of an Andalusian cortijo, she is wooed by several men of the village, among them the young Joselillo. But The Cat only feels love for Juan, a handsome and cocky worker who dreams of being a bullfighter.

Title: 260. Comanche
description: Common efforts of the U.S. government and the Comanche nation to negotiate a peace treaty are sabotaged by renegade Indians and by the short-sighted Indian Commissioner (Lowell Gilmore).

Title: 261. Panic in the Parlor
description: Emma interrupts Albert's bachelor party, he gets cold feet about marrying her daughter. Unsure if Emma's vow to change will last, Albert marries Shirley anyway.

Title: 262. Carnival Night
description: A new chief of a "Culture House" is planning to hold a terribly boring New Year concert. A group of young amateur actors are doing their best to liven up the concert.

Title: 263. Private's Progress
description: In World War II, a failed British officer is selected by his uncle, a brigadier with the War Office, to participate in a secret operation to recover looted artwork from the Germans.

Title: 264. Mohawk
description: In 1700s New York, a Boston artist working in the remote Fort Alden is torn between his love for 2 women and thrown into the middle of a Mohawk-Iroquois-American war.

Title: 265. A Party in Hell
description: Hajji Jabbar is a miser, greedy and disliked businessman. He tries to make more money by any means even by forcing her daughter to marry a rich old man rather than let her marry her cousin Hamid that she loves. Jabbar suddenly becomes sick and sees grim reaper who takes him to see hell in a long sequence. When Hajji Jabbar awakes he changes and tries to redeem himself.

Title: 266. The Girl He Left Behind
description: Privileged college student Andy Shaeffer is a mama's boy who flunks out of school and is drafted by the army where he becomes a real man, to the astonishment of everyone.

Title: 267. Diane
description: In the sixteenth century, a noblewoman has a love affair with the French King.

Title: 268. Des gens sans importance
description: Mid-aged married truck driver falls in love with a young waitress he meets while making a break on a long trip. They try to make it work, but she can't get a decent job or place to stay in his town. Things get worse when the man gets fired and his family find out. And there's more complications to follow for both of them...

Title: 269. Man Beast
description: Connie Hayward mounts an expedition into the Himalayan Mountains looking for her brother, who has not returned from a previous trek trying to locate the Yeti, or "Abominable Snowman". Arriving at her brother's last-known camp Connie and her companions find only a strange old guide, Varga. They are soon attacked by gigantic Snowmen but are not half as surprised as when Vargas reveals his secret origin and the plans he has for Connie.

Title: 270. The Animal World
description: A documentary showcasing the world's many different animal species, both past and present.

Title: 271. Gun for a Coward
description: After the death of a rancher, his three sons run the ranch but one of them is seen as a coward because of his aversion to gun-fighting.

Title: 272. Rice Girl
description: A young girl hires herself for a low salary in order to snare herself in the rice fields. By the way, the landlord is also her unknown father, of whom she should know nothing. He stands by her paternal as she gets into trouble.

Title: 273. Jacqueline
description: Captivating drama of a lovable little Irish girl and how she helps her tippler father find work.

Title: 274. The Birds and the Bees
description: On an ocean voyage, a card shark and her father cheat a naive man out of his money. Things take a twist when the girl falls in love with the man she's just fleeced.

Title: 275. Dark Waters
description: After three years of absence, back (Recep) after a long travel trip spent on the back of one of the ships in an effort to save money in order to complete his marriage b (benign), who lives with his mother in a shack built on the sea, but with the passage of days legged in the heart of (Recep) feelings of jealousy when he doubted the existence of a relationship between the pool (benign), and between (Mamdouh) son of the owner of the shipping company, which coincided with the existence of many problems between the owner of the company and its employees.

Title: 276. That Certain Feeling
description: Divorced comic strip cartoonist Francis X. Dignan is hired as a ghost-writer by pompous client Larry Larkin who happens to be the fiancé of Dignan's ex-wife.

Title: 277. The Black Tent
description: In the African desert, a British soldier romances a native chief's daughter and helps the tribe fight off a German attack.

Title: 278. Los gavilanes
description: Dos hombres que desean a la misma mujer no saben que son medios hermanos. Uno de ellos pertenece a Los Gavilanes, una pandilla de bandoleros que viven escondidos y saquean a los ricos para darles a los pobres.

Title: 279. Francis in the Haunted House
description: Francis the Talking Mule witnesses a murder. He takes a bumbling reporter named David Prescott under his wing and the two of them set out to solve the crime.

Title: 280. The Great Man
description: Joe Harris, preparing a eulogy for popular radio commentator Herb Fuller, finds that nobody has a good word to say about him.

Title: 281. Odongo: An Adventure of the African Frontier
description: In Kenya, a white trader of exotic animals is mentoring and caring for an African boy but is annoyed by his new female replacement veterinarian and must deal with a disgruntled former employee.

Title: 282. Flowing
description: Otsuta is running the geisha house Tsuta in Tokyo. Her business is heavily in debt. Her daughter Katsuyo doesn't see any future in her mothers trade in the late days of Geisha. But Otsuta will not give up. This film portraits the day time life of geisha when not entertaining customers.

Title: 283. Flesh and the Spur
description: A young cowboy searches for the killer of his twin brother.

Title: 284. Totò, Peppino e la... malafemmina
description: Two clumsy provincial uncles visit a metropolis to stop the relationship between their nephew and a woman of ill repute.

Title: 285. El inocente
description: Mane's car breaks down on New Year's Eve. Mechanic Cruci gives her a ride. They get drunk, sleep together. Mane's parents arrive, misunderstand, force them to marry against their will.

Title: 286. The Cruel Tower
description: Tension and rivalry among a crew of steeplejacks.

Title: 287. Rebel in Town
description: After the Civil War, five Confederates find trouble in a Yankee town when one of them accidentally shoots and kills a young local boy.

Title: 288. Gaby
description: A French ballerina (Leslie Caron) in 1944 London falls for an American soldier (John Kerr) who is sent to France in the Normandy Invasion.

Title: 289. Satellite in the Sky
description: The British launch the world's first orbital vehicle. Their military sends a super-bomb along, which goes wrong and threatens the crew and a stowaway.

Title: 290. Hidden Guns
description: The outlaw Stragg has the town so intimidated that no one will speak against him no matter what he does. Sheriff Young heads for a nearby town, where there is a witness willing to testify. Meanwhile, Stragg hires a gunman to take care of the sheriff and the witness.

Title: 291. It's Great to Be Young!
description: It's heaven at Angel Hill Grammar School until the arrival of the new headmaster, Mr. Frome, who prohibits sixth formers from their beloved music-making. Dingle, a very unconventional music master, helps the students in their time of need.

Title: 292. A Strange Adventure
description: A trio of thieves make their getaway by kidnapping a young hot-rodder, and take over a mountain cabin for a hideout after overpowering its occupants.

Title: 293. Blonde Bait
description: U.S. agent Kent Foster pursues traitorous murderer Nick Randall using singer Angela Booth as bait. Angela escapes prison with Foster's help to meet Randall on New Year's Eve but flees after Randall assaults her, confirming his true nature.

Title: 294. If All the Guys in the World...
description: Crew members of a French fishing ship in the North Sea fall ill one by one, poisoned by rotten meat. They can only survive by getting serum within the following hours. Joint actions of rescuers from different countries commence.

Title: 295. Canyon River
description: While a Wyoming rancher goes to Oregon to buy cattle, his foreman and a gang of town criminals plot together to steal the herd, but the rancher's hired cattle drive hands are old convicts and rustlers themselves.

Title: 296. Breakaway
description: Suave veteran private eye Duke Martin is on the trail of a secret formula and a kidnapped girl.

Title: 297. Up in the World
description: A friendly window cleaner works at an English country estate where he saves the owner's son from kidnappers.

Title: 298. El fantasma de la casa roja
description: A millionaire's ghost watches while his heirs murder each other over his fortune.

Title: 299. Stranger at My Door
description: Chased by a posse, bank robber Clay Anderson, traveling under an assumed name, takes refuge at a farm owned by a preacher and his pretty young wife.

Title: 300. Halaku
description: Halaku (Pran), the powerful emperor of Iran, rules the country wisely and with an iron hand. When he comes upon one of his subjects, Niloufer (Meena Kumari), he stakes his claim on her and wants her to be his wife, despite of his wife (Minoo Mumtaz), who opposes his marriage plans. Niloufer, who loves Pervez (Ajit), refuses to submit to Halaku, he turns his wrath on both Niloufer, Pervez, and his wife. Will Niloufer and Pervez survive the ruthless Halaku? Notable song is "AAja ke intezar main jaane ko hai bahar bhi, tere vegar zindagi dard banke ke rahey gai..." in the evergreen voice of Mohd. Rafi.

Title: 301. Sudden Rain
description: This wry chamber piece from director Mikio Naruse focuses on a couple whose pet peeves and minor irritations escalate into major rifts and animosity.

Title: 302. The First Texan
description: Eastern lawyer Sam Houston moves to Texas. At the request of President Jackson, he leads the Texan independence movement and wins the decisive battle against the Mexican army to gain Texas independence.

Title: 303. The Price of Fear
description: The co-owner of a dog track is framed for two crimes: the shotgun killing of his ex-partner and the hit-and-run death of an elderly man.

Title: 304. Teenage Rebel
description: Nancy Fallon gets custody of her teenage daughter Dodie back from her ex-husband after she remarries, but she must win her love.

Title: 305. The Rocket from Calabuch
description: Professor Jorge Serra Hamilton, an American atomic-bomb specialist, flees from his transcendental duties to take shelter incognito in Calabuch, a small, idyllic Spanish village on the Mediterranean shores. Oblivious to their guest's eminence, local residents spend their time engaged in their modest daily chores. The affable Professor Hamilton not only integrates perfectly into the small town, forging deep friendships with his neighbors, but he might also be finding the happiness he craves.

Title: 306. The Spanish Gardener
description: Rather undiplomatic British diplomat Harrington Brande (Sir Michael Hordern) takes up his new post in Spain accompanied by his son Nicholas (Jon Whiteley). The posting is something of a disappointment to Harrington, who was hoping for a promotion. That his wife had left him seems to have affected his career. Nicholas sees it all as something of an adventure, and soon becomes fast friends with the new gardener, José (Sir Dirk Bogarde). The apparently "delicate" Nicholas becomes attached to José, and Harrington's jealousy leads him to bar Nicholas from even speaking to José. As tensions mount, another servant frames José for theft, forcing everyone to review the situation.

Title: 307. Merry-Go-Round
description: In a rural scenery in the throes of difficult changes lives a humble but promising young farmer girl called Mari Pataki. Her father forbids her from seeing the man she loves. The father, above all preoccupied by work on the fields and prospective wealth, decides to give his daughter in marriage to an old but rich man with whom he does business. Land marries land, he says. This seems to be the unyielding rule of the Hungarian peasantry. But the young lover is ready to stand up to any challenge to keep Maris love.

Title: 309. The Vagabond King
description: Louis XI of France drafts Paris's popular king of criminals as Provost Marshal in his fight against usurper Charles of Burgundy and the traitorous nobles who rally around him.

Title: 310. Crime and Punishment
description: Modern update of Dostoievski's novel Crime and Punishment.

Title: 311. One Wish Too Many
description: A young boy finds a magic marble that grants him any wish he wants. One day he wishes for a giant steam-roller, and it starts to trash London.

Title: 312. Parivar
description: A joint family consisting of four brothers, their wives, and their respective children, living under one roof. Some of the brothers are professionls, one a lawyer, a doctor, and others businessmen. They are a happy family, living and sharing each other's joys and sorrows. Then one day, an arguement breaks out over a glass of milk, and the entire family is thrown into chaos, and the only resolution seems to be nothing but dividing the entire property amongst the brothers and their respective families.

Title: 313. Rumble on the Docks
description: Crime drama concerning the coming-of-age of a Brooklyn-born 17-year old whose loyalty is torn between his parents' old-fashion values and a local gangster's flashy lifestyle.

Title: 314. Jan Zizka
description: Empowered by the teachings of Jan Hus, Jan Zizka launches a relentless guerrilla war against the followers of Emperor Sigismund as he attempts to unite the people of Prague behind the Hussite cause.

Title: 315. The Kettles in the Ozarks
description: Ma and the kids head back to the Ozarks for a visit with Pa's brother Uncle Sedge, who's working his way through a 20-year-long relationship with Miss Bedelia Baines.

Title: 316. Valley of Peace
description: During WWII in Slovenia, two orphaned children seeking the imaginary Valley of Peace run into a downed black American pilot who tries to protect them from the Germans until the Yugoslav Partisans can arrive.

Title: 317. The Best Things in Life Are Free
description: Ray joins Buddy and Lew to form a successful 1920s musical show writing team. Soon, they've got several hits on Broadway, but Buddy's ambition leads to friction among the group, as the other 2 feel increasingly left out.

Title: 318. A Day of Fury
description: When gunslinger Jagade arrives in a law-abiding god-fearing town he manages to turn the townsfolk into scoff-law sinners while the town Marshal is powerless due to a moral debt to Jagade.

Title: 320. Bonjour Kathrin
description: Three young penniless musicians travel to San Remo to work as hotel clerks and to get a chance to show their talent on the San Remo festival.

Title: 321. Isle of Levant
description: A documentary on the island off the French Riviera where 'bathing in the buff' isn't just practiced, it's highly encouraged!

Title: 322. Eyewitness
description: Lucy Church, the sole witness to a fatal robbery, is struck by a passing bus and her life lies in the balance as the thieves wait for a chance to finish her off.

Title: 323. The Rawhide Years
description: Dishonest riverboat gambler Ben Matthews is blamed for a murder he didn't commit and must find the real killer before the lynch mob finds him.

Title: 324. Toto Double or Nothing
description: The Duke Gagliardo della Forcoletta, penniless and expert in horse-races, finds out he has a daughter, Emma Marini, who works in the bar Aurora. The Duke decides to participate in "Lascia o Raddoppia," a TV quiz transmission, in order to win the five million lira necessary to buy the bar, and he becomes famous. Gangsters Nick Molise and Joe Taccola bet between themselves on his success and the Duke is kidnapped.

Title: 325. Uranium Boom
description: A love triangle tears apart two partners prospecting for uranium in Colorado.

Title: 326. Dance with Me, Henry
description: Two goofballs try to run a beaten-down old amusement park.

Title: 327. Los platillos voladores
description: A guy and his girlfriend pretend to come from Mars.

Title: 328. Castle of the Banned Lovers
description: The beautiful Beatrice Cenci, daughter of the noble Francesco, falls in love with the intendant Olimpio. But she has to face the jealousy of her violent and morbid father, and the hostility of her stepmother Lucrezia.

Title: 329. Far til fire i byen
description: The last day of the summer holiday is spent in the amusement park.

Title: 330. The Thick-Walled Room
description: A group of rank-and-file Japanese soldiers are jailed for crimes against humanity, themselves victims of a nation refusing to bear its burdens as a whole.

Title: 331. I Will Buy You
description: A talent scout moves sharply, dead-set on signing a promising athlete to his team.

Title: 332. Madame White Snake
description: Lavish Japanese-Chinese coproduction based on an ancient Chinese legend about a man who falls in love with a snake goddess in human form.

Title: 333. Child in the House
description: Young Elizabeth is left with her relatives, a married couple, while her mother is in the hospital. The friendly husband likes her, but the wife hates kids. One day her father, an often-absent crook on the lam, visits her in secret.

Title: 334. Circus Friends
description: When Marlow's circus comes to town they find that the field they usually use is not available because they didn't pay the farmer last year. They have to promise most of their equipment to the farmer as surety and will only get it back if they do extra business this year. The circus children and their friends decide to help make this season a success.

Title: 335. Fighting Trouble
description: "Sach" has become a camera fiend so, in the pursuit of some ready cash, "Duke" takes him and his photographs to the editor of the New York Morning Blade, Mr. Ray Vance. He hires them to get some photos of gangland boss Frankie Arbo but Mr. Arbo does not care to have his picture in the papers and dislikes cameramen for the same reason. "Sach" and "Duke" pose as interior decorators in the penthouse of Mae Randall in order to get photos of Arbo. Later, at Arbo's night club, the boys learn that the gangster is importing a tough hoodlum from Chicago. "Sach" and "Duke" lure the visiting gunman, Handsome Hal Lomax to Mrs. Kelly's boardinghouse and trick him into staying there through false police calls. "Sach" masquerades as Handsome Hal and gets away with it, and he and "Duke" manage to get into Arbo's inner office with the Boss and his henchmen, and the boys are cut into the gang's racket, which is counterfeit money. Then Handsome Hal shows up and things are getting dicey for the boys until Handsome Hal's jilted sweetheart, Dolly Tate makes her appearance, and she is so put out with getting jilted by the real Handsome Hal that she identifies "Sach" as the real Handsome Hal, and fingers Handsome himself as the impostor.. "Sach" has been taking photos with a miniature camera hidden in his cigarette holder, but accidentally unloads the camera, and the film falls out, exposing the boys and the film.

Title: 336. The Lebanese Mission
description: Jean Servais and Omar Sharif are explorers searching for uranium in the Arabian desert. They run into spies, thieves and two attractive mysterious women played by Juliette Greco and Luciana Paluzzi.

Title: 337. Chandrakanta
description: Veerjal vanqishes Chandrakanta (Bina Rai) father and takes over his kingdom. On insisting on seeing the most beautiful girl in the land, he is told it is none other than Chandrakanta. To get her to come to him, he whips her father till Chandrakanta voluntarily comes to him and executes a dance at the end of which she is unsuccessful in her attempt to kill Veerjal. He responds by killing Chandrakanta's father in front of her eyes. She escapes swearing revenge. Landing up in a remote ashram, she meets and falls in love with Kunal(Bharat Bhushan). When news reaches her of Veerjal's increasing tyranny, she remembers her vow and rouses the people against Veerjal. Finally all's well that ends well as Veerjal is killed and Chandrakanta and Kunal are united.

Title: 338. Runaway Daughters
description: Three teenagers with troubled families are unable to adjust at home and in high-school. Tempted with an easy, carefree life they soon pass from misdemeanors into serious crime - and will suffer for it. Sometimes, repentance comes too late.

Title: 339. I've Lived Before
description: An airline pilot believes he's a pilot who was killed during WW I.

Title: 340. The Ghost of Yotsuya
description: Oiwa has been searching for the one who killed her father for a long time. She comes to Yedo and sees a man named Naosuke. The film is based on the kabuki classic: Toukaidou Yotsuya Kaidan (1826) written by Tsuruya Nanboku and is one of the most famous ghost stories throughout Japan.

Title: 341. Keep It Clean
description: A man invents a new cleaning machine. His brother in law offers to help him promote it and they get help from the Purity League.

Title: 342. The Brass Legend
description: An honest sheriff attempts to save an 11-year-old boy who helped him capture a notorious killer.

Title: 343. A Touch of the Sun
description: Willie is a hall porter who is left a fortune but after living it up for a while he returns to his old hotel which is in financial difficulties.

Title: 344. The White Squaw
description: Faced with heavy opposition from local ranchers, a white Indian woman desperately seeks help for her tribe struggling to survive on a reservation.

Title: 345. Flight to Hong Kong
description: Macao organized crime under-boss Tony Dumont rips the Syndicate off and disappears with a load of diamonds but the Syndicate men and the Hong-Kong police are chasing him around the world.

Title: 346. Donatella
description: Donatella is a simple and honest Roman girl, daughter of a bookbinder and girlfriend of Guido, a gas station owner.

Title: 347. The Kreutzer Sonata
description: In this adaptation of Tolstoy's argument for sexual abstinence, a man recounts the events that led to the killing of his wife.

Title: 348. Vesna na Zarechnoy ulitse
description: A newly appointed Russian literature teacher develops a strong connection with one of her flagging students.

Title: 349. Wetbacks
description: Hard on his luck, a fishing charter boat captain unwisely gets involved with a crime ring smuggling illegal Mexicans into California.

Title: 350. Screaming Eagles
description: "Screaming Eagles" is a historical drama about paratroopers of the 101st Airborne Division fighting during the D-Day Invasion in June of 1944. The title was the Division's nickname.

Title: 351. Kyûketsu-ga
description: The story of a professional nude model stalked by a bizarre, unknown man wearing a hideous mask.

Title: 352. Johnny Concho
description: After two desperadoes take a town hostage, former bad boy Johnny Concho, brother of a notorious gunfighter, must find the courage to save it.

Title: 353. Bhai-Bhai
description: Widowed Dayashankar is a businessman who lives in Madras with his two school-going sons, Raj and Ashok.
